---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const linkedin = "https://www.linkedin.com/in/jake-herridge-2722b139";
const github = "https://github.com/jakelherridge";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Jake Herridge is an operations leader and AI builder. Ten years scaling an engineering staffing firm, now writing and shipping what he learns with AI."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-5 py-16">
    <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl tracking-tight md:text-5xl">Hi, I'm Jake.</h1>

    <div class="paper-body mt-8">
      <p>
        I spent the last ten years at an engineering staffing firm called LER TechForce, most of it
        as the director of operations. Director of operations by title, chief of staff in scope. I
        reported to the CEO, sat on the leadership team, and owned how the company actually ran.
      </p>
      <p>
        When I started, we were a $22 million company with 180 engineers in the field. When I left,
        we were at $75 million and more than 550, and our internal headcount had not grown. I built
        the analytics, the forecasting, and the governance that let us scale like that without the
        back office scaling with it. The work I am proudest of is the work nobody noticed, because it
        just ran.
      </p>
      <p>
        A few years in, I became the person who brought AI into the business. Not as a slide deck, as
        tools people used on a Tuesday. I designed an internal AI hub that put every tool we built
        behind one door. I built an automated performance-review system that covers more than 500
        people and saves over 2,000 hours a cycle. I built margin calculators, document formatters,
        and an agent that reads a resume and goes and finds the roles that fit it. Most of it I built
        by directing Claude Code, with no developer in the loop.
      </p>
      <p>
        Here is the thing I keep coming back to. The big idea is almost always buried in the day to
        day, in the boring parts everyone has stopped looking at. The part of the job I love is
        finding it and building it. AI is the best lever I have ever had for that. It takes the boring
        work off people so they can do the work that is actually human.
      </p>
      <p>
        Outside of work I build. I made PocketWild, an iOS field journal, end to end as a non-coder,
        by directing the AI and drawing the pixel art myself. I help my wife run her cooking brand. I
        have started a stack of white papers. I have also failed at plenty: a 3D image app, a
        color-palette tool, a wage-and-classification generator, a few others. I am fine with that.
        Every one taught me something I used in the next thing.
      </p>
      <p>
        I am an electrical engineer with an MBA, both from Harding. I live in Bentonville, Arkansas,
        with my wife and our four kids. This is home. The rest is just me trying to build useful
        things, and learn out loud while I do it.
      </p>
    </div>

    <dl
      class="mt-12 grid grid-cols-1 gap-x-8 gap-y-5 border-t border-faint pt-8 text-sm sm:grid-cols-2"
    >
      <div>
        <dt class="text-muted">Education</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1">B.S. Electrical Engineering and MBA, Harding University</dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt class="text-muted">Certifications</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1">Anthropic AI Fluency, Teaching AI Fluency, Agent Skills, Subagents</dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt class="text-muted">Based in</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1">Bentonville, Arkansas</dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt class="text-muted">Find me</dt>
        <dd class="mt-1">
          <a href={linkedin} rel="me noopener" class="text-accent underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-accent-strong">LinkedIn</a>,
          <a href={github} rel="me noopener" class="text-accent underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-accent-strong">GitHub</a>
        </dd>
      </div>
    </dl>

    <div class="mt-12">
      <a
        href="/contact/"
        class="inline-flex items-center rounded bg-accent px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-medium text-white transition-colors hover:bg-accent-strong"
      >
        Get in touch
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
